# Cursos — core rules

Follow [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) and existing code in the same package.

## Stack

- Quarkus REST + Hibernate ORM + PostgreSQL + Flyway.
- Angular SPA via Quinoa (`src/main/webui/`).
- **Passport JWT** (SmallRye JWT validates Passport-issued tokens); API base path `/api`.
- Cursos dev port **8083**; Passport **8080**.

## Endpoints

- `@ApplicationScoped` + `@Path`; suffix `*Endpoint`.
- Constructor injection for repositories and services.
- HTTP body types: Java `record`, suffix `Request` / `Response` — [cursos-http-contract.mdc](cursos-http-contract.mdc).
- Response mapping: static `load()` factory on `*Response` records.
- Security: `@DenyAll` on class + `@Authenticated` or `@RolesAllowed` on methods; teacher/student checks in services.

## Data access

- Repositories: `EntityManager` directly; `Optional` for single results; `@Transactional` on mutating methods — [cursos-jpa.mdc](cursos-jpa.mdc).
- Domain logic: `@ApplicationScoped` `*Service` (e.g. `CourseService`, `EnrollmentService`, `ProgressService`, `MailerService`).

## Frontend

- Services in `src/main/webui/src/app/services/` — HTTP calls to `/api`.
- Components by feature folder under `components/`.
- Auth: Passport login → JWT in `auth.interceptor.ts` Bearer header.

## Never

- `System.out.println` — use SLF4J.
- Raw `VO`/`DTO` suffix on HTTP types.
- Hardcode new API paths in multiple Angular files — centralize in services.
- Implement local password login — identity lives in Passport.

## When adding a feature

[development-process.mdc](development-process.mdc) — feature analysis → architecture design → task break → **explicit task approval** → TDD. Then ARCHITECTURE.md §13 — domain spec → package → tests → endpoint → Angular service/component → feature catalog.

## When fixing a test

Understand failure first; fix production code or test data via `Given`. Do not weaken assertions.
